            <a name="usage"/>
            <subsection name="Usage">
                <ol type="1">
                    <li>Unzip
                        <tt>jpbc-1.2.0.zip</tt>
                        to the directory you wish to unzip it.
                    </li>
                    <li>To use jPBC add to your classpath the following jars:
                        <ol type="1">
                            <li>
                                <font style="font-weight: bold;color:red"><tt>jpbc_1.2.0-api.jar</tt></font>
                                and
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                <font style="font-weight: bold;color:red"><tt>jpbc_1.2.0-plaf.jar</tt></font>.
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                        To use the wrapper include also
                        <ol>
                            <li>
                                <font style="font-weight: bold;color:green"><tt>jpbc_1.2.0-pbc.jar</tt></font>
                                and
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                <font style="font-weight: bold;color:green"><tt>jna-3.1.0.jar</tt></font>.
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                        Remember that to use the wrapper you must compile the shared library
                        to enable the communication between PBC and jPBC. Go
                        <a href="./docs/pbcwrapper.html">here</a>
                        to see how to do that.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        If you want to use the implemented 
                        <a href="schemes/schemes.html">pairing based crypto-systems</a>
                        include:
                        <ol>
                            <li>
                                <font style="font-weight: bold;color:green"><tt>jpbc_1.2.0-crypto.jar</tt></font>
                                and
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <font style="font-weight: bold;color:green"><tt>bcprov-jdk16-140.jar</tt></font>.
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                </ol>
                <p>
                    All these libraries can be found in the jars folder.
                </p>
            </subsection>

